.SH "NAME"
DROP_INDEX \- remove an index
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.nf
DROP INDEX [ IF EXISTS ] \fIname\fR [, \&.\&.\&.] [ CASCADE | RESTRICT ]
.fi
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
DROP INDEX
drops an existing index from the database system\&. To execute this command you must be the owner of the index\&.
.SH "PARAMETERS"
.PP
IF EXISTS
.RS 4
Do not throw an error if the index does not exist\&. A notice is issued in this case\&.
.RE
.PP
\fIname\fR
.RS 4
The name (optionally schema\-qualified) of an index to remove\&.
.RE
.PP
CASCADE
.RS 4
Automatically drop objects that depend on the index\&.
.RE
.PP
RESTRICT
.RS 4
Refuse to drop the index if any objects depend on it\&. This is the default\&.
.RE
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.PP
This command will remove the index
title_idx:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
DROP INDEX title_idx;
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.SH "COMPATIBILITY"
.PP
DROP INDEX
